text.section:
To establish a broker's lien under this subtitle, a broker shall commence proceedings in the circuit court where the commercial property is located within 180 days after the commercial leasing commission became due and payable by filing with the clerk of the court:
A petition to establish a broker's lien, which shall contain the following:
The name and address of the petitioner;
The name and address of the owner;
A copy of the brokerage agreement;
A description of the lien property, including a statement whether part of the lien property is located in another county, by:
The amount of the commission and the unpaid portion of the commission;
An affidavit by the broker or by an individual on behalf of the broker stating the facts which the broker is claiming a broker's lien against the lien property in the amount specified; and
Either original or sworn, certified or photostatic copies of all material papers or parts of any material papers, if any, which constitute the basis of the broker's claim for a lien, unless the absence of any material papers or parts of any material papers is explained in the affidavit.
